7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1168, L.D. 1750, “An Act to Require
10 the Attorney General to Create and Update Biennially a Model Residential Lease”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 14 MRSA §6030-K is enacted to read:
14 §6030-K. Model residential lease
15 1. Model residential lease. By December 1, 2025, the Attorney General shall create
16 and post on the Attorney General's publicly accessible website a model lease for residential
17 property that complies with current law, including any disclosure and any document
18 required to be attached to a residential lease. The Attorney General shall update the model
19 lease biennially and post the revised model lease no later than December 1st of every odd-
20 numbered year.
21 2. Implementation. The Attorney General shall implement this section within
22 existing resources.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment removes from the bill the requirement that the model lease posted by
2277 the Attorney General must be neutral and the requirement that the Attorney General post
2288 the model lease for public comment. The amendment also removes language from the bill
2299 that requires the Attorney General to consult with one or more tenant advocacy and landlord
3300 advocacy organizations when creating or revising the model lease. Finally, the amendment
3311 requires the Attorney General to create and update the model lease within existing
3322 resources.
3333 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3344 (See attached)
